{"lemma": "دِرْهَمٌ", "slug": "دِرْهَمٌ", "root": "NTWS", "root_slug": "NTWS", "root_link": "/words/roots/NTWS", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 1}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n12502"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%90%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%87%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "dirham", "fa": "درهم", "ur": "درہم", "tr": "dirhem", "id": "dirham", "bn": "দিরহাম", "es": "dirham", "fr": "dirham", "de": "Dirham", "ru": "дирхам", "zh": "迪拉姆"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "dirham"}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Etymology tree\nMiddle Persian 𐭦𐭥𐭦𐭭 (drahm)bor.\nArabic درهم\nBorrowed from Middle Persian 𐭦𐭥𐭦𐭭 (drahm)."}, "ipa": ["/dir.ham/", "/dar.ham/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n12502", "headword_ar": "دِرْهَمٌ", "root": "drhm", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) of the measure"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiEolalN", "text_ar": "فِعْلَلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb, MF,) of which it has been said that there are only three other instances, but there are many more; (MF;) an arabicized word, (S, Msb,) from the Pers. ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "diramo", "text_ar": "دِرَمْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (S;) also pronounced ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dirohimN", "text_ar": "دِرْهِمٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb, K,) but this is of rare occurrence; (TA;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dirohaAmN", "text_ar": "دِرْهَامٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, K,) which is more rare; (TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain silver coin;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, Msb;) like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "diynaArN", "text_ar": "دِينَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies a certain gold coin: (Mgh:) [and the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "weight thereof;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a drachm,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dram:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its weight is six"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dawaAniyq", "text_ar": "دَوَانِيق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dániks"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (Msb, and K in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mk", "text_ar": "مك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ";) i. e.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the weight of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "diroham A_isolaAmiY~", "text_ar": "دِرْهَم اـِسْلَامِىّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": but in the Time of Ignorance, some dirhems were light, being"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "four"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dwAnyq", "text_ar": "دوانيق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and these were called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tabariy~apN", "text_ar": "طَبَرِيَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and some were heavy, being"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "eight"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dwAnyq", "text_ar": "دوانيق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and these were called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eabodiy~apN", "text_ar": "عَبْدِيَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bagoliy~apN", "text_ar": "بَغْلِيَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": and of these two they made two that were equal; so that each"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "drhm", "text_ar": "درهم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "was"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "six"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dwAnyq", "text_ar": "دوانيق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": this is said to have been done by 'Omar: or, accord. to another account, some dirhems were of the weight of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "twenty carats,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and were called the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "weight of ten"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e. of ten"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "dániks"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; and some were of the weight of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ten"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "carats"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], and were called the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "weight of five;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and some were of the weight of"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "twelve"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "carats"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], and were called the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "weight of six;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and they put the three weights together, and called the third part thereof the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "weight of seven:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and one of the weights of the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "drhm", "text_ar": "درهم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "before El-Islám was"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "twelve carats,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "which is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "six"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dwAnyq", "text_ar": "دوانيق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": but the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "drhm AslAmY~", "text_ar": "درهم اسلامىّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "sixteen carats;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dAnq", "text_ar": "دانق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of this being a carat and two thirds: (Msb:) or dirhems should be"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fourteen carats"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "seven dániks"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; ten being of the weight of seven"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mavaAqiyl", "text_ar": "مَثَاقِيل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or mithkáls]: in the Time of Ignorance, some were heavy, [equal to]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mvAqyl", "text_ar": "مثاقيل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and some were light, [called]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Tabariy~apN", "text_ar": "طَبَرِيَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and when they were coined in the age of El-Islám, they made of the heavy and the light two dirhems, so that ten became equal to seven"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mvAqyl", "text_ar": "مثاقيل"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": A 'Obeyd says that this was done in the time [of the dynasty] of the sons of Umeiyeh: (El-Karkhee, cited in the Mgh:) [see also De Sacy's “ Chrest. Arabe, ” sec. ed., vol. ii. p. 110 of the Arabic text, and p. 282 of the transl.; where it is further stated, on the authority of Ibn-Khaldoon, that the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "diroham magoribiY~", "text_ar": "دِرْهَم مَغْرِبِىّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "was"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "three"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dwAnyq", "text_ar": "دوانيق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yamaniY~", "text_ar": "يَمَنِىّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ","}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "one"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dAnq", "text_ar": "دانق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; and, as is said in the Msb, that 'Omar adopted the mean between the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bglY~", "text_ar": "بغلىّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "TbrY~", "text_ar": "طبرىّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", making the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "drhm", "text_ar": "درهم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "to be"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "six:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] the pl. (of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "drhm", "text_ar": "درهم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", S) is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daraAhimu", "text_ar": "دَرَاهِمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and (of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "drhAm", "text_ar": "درهام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", S)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daraAhiymu", "text_ar": "دَرَاهِيمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, K.) [The former of these pls. is often used as signifying"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Money, cash,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "coin,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in an absolute sense.] The dim. is ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "durayohimN", "text_ar": "دُرَيْهِمٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "durayohiymN", "text_ar": "دُرَيْهِيمٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": the latter held by Sb to be anomalous; for he says that it is as though it were formed from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dirohaAmN", "text_ar": "دِرْهَامٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", though this was not used by them. (TA.) ―         -b2-  Hence, as being likened thereto, [i. e., to the coin thus called,] (TA,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dirohamN", "text_ar": "دِرْهَمٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies also (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Hadiyqap", "text_ar": "حَدِيقَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[app. as meaning a"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "round piece of land surrounded by a fence or the like,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "by elevated land;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for this is one of the significations of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HadiyqapN", "text_ar": "حَدِيقَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (K.) [It is said that] this is taken from"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 877}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the saying of 'Antarah, [describing shower of copious rain,]"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "fatarakona kul~a HadiyqapK kaAld~irohami"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "So that they left every ridged-round spot of ground like the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "drhm", "text_ar": "درهم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) [But accord. to one reading, he said,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kul~a qaraArapK", "text_ar": "كُلَّ قَرَارَةٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; meaning, as is said in the EM, p. 227, “ every round hollow; ” and likening such a hollow to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "drhm", "text_ar": "درهم"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because of its roundness, and the clearness and whiteness of its water.]"}], "source_refs": ["S", "Mgh", "Msb", "K", "MF", "TA"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-14", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}